Description:
Worked with Human Digital Team to develop digital twin through deep learning-based, real-time motion trackers. 
After 2023 summer, continued as a Capstone Project. For the first time, a joint project and connection between CSIRO and The University of Melbourne was established.
2024 summer, worked as RA to finish the project.
Taught content of Machine Learning (COMP30027), Introduction to Machine Learning (COMP90049), Computer Vision (COMP90086), and its basic implementations in Python libraries.

Managed the code infrastructure (full-stack work and algorithm development) of the product software for a German broadcasting company, and worked with international clients (mostly Europe). Informally, that was fixing bugs day by day.
Worked under Dr.Thu-Anh Nguyen, on modelling COVID-19 situation in Vietnam.
Worked under Professor Andrew Ooi, on the topic of Gravitational Current Simulation ("Entrainment and Mixing of Gravity Currents in a Stratified Ambient" - A. Ooi et al., 12th AHMTC, 2021).

Trained as a developer in the DevOps team and infrastructure department, and operated the automation of server production. Have also compiled a guide to introductory server learning for later interns.
